name: method
description: An optional method to call. In the ``class`` case the method can be static. If the method is static the class is not instantiated and if ``init`` or ``properties`` are present it results in an exception.

name: property
description: Context property name. Mutually exclusive with ``class`` and ``service``. One of ``class``, ``property``, or ``service`` is required.

name: service
description: Fully qualified context service class name. Mutually exclusive with ``class`` and ``property``. One of ``class``, ``property``, or ``service`` is required.

name: type
description:
Fully qualified class name. Mutually exclusive with ``service`` and ``property``. One of ``class``, ``property``, or ``service`` is required.

For SupplierFactory adapter, if the class implements SupplierFactory then it is instantiated and then its ``create()`` method is invoked to create a supplier.
If the class implements Supplier, then it is instantiated. If there are no ``init`` arguments, then the supplier is diagnosed as part of ``diagnose()``. 
Otherwise it is diagnosed in ``execute()`` and diagnostic results are discarded.

Similar processing will be implemented for Consumer and Command.

name: arguments
description: An optional array of method arguments. If elements implement SupplierFactory, then the factory is used to produce argument value. Then arguments get converted to method parameter types if conversion is available. If conversion is not available, an exception is thrown.

name: init
description: An optional array of constructor arguments for the ``class``. Not applicable for ``property`` and ``service``. If elements implement SupplierFactory then the factory is used to produce argument values. Then arguments get converted to constructor parameter types if conversion is available. If conversion is not available, an exception is thrown.

name: properties
description: A map injected into the instance in the ``class`` case if the instance implements ${javadoc/java.util.function.BiConsumer} or in the service or property case if they implement SupplierFactory. If elements implement SupplierFactory then the supplier factory is used to produce value to be injected. Otherwise elements are injected AS-IS.

name: Interpolator
description: Converts input stream to String using the context charset, which defaults to ``UTF-8``, interpolates, and converts back to input stream using the context charset.

name: base
description:
Optional base URL for resolving include and image URL's. 
If the base is blank then marker location is used as the base, if marker is present and location is not null. 
Otherwise, resource URL is used as the base. 
Marker location is the URL of a YAML resource from which interpolator specification was loaded. 
It may be different from the resource URL if a model was loaded from YAML and then saved to XML.

If the base is not blank then it is resolved relative to the marker location if it starts with ``./`` and marker location is not null or the resource base otherwise.

name: ReconcileAction
description: Defines an action to take when a resource with the same name already exists.

name: Append
description: Appends new content to the existing content. For containers it means that new resources will be placed in the container next to the existing resources. For files it means that the new content will be appended after the existing content.

name: Cancel
description: Cancels execution if resource already exists.

name: Keep
description: Keeps the existing resource intact.

name: Merge
description: Merges old and new content of a file using a built-in or provided ``org.nasdanika.common.resources.Merger``. Merger is obtained from ``merger`` reference. For containers Merge is the same as Append.

name: Overwrite
description: Overwrites existing resource. For containers - deletes their contents.

name: Rename
description: Renames existing resource. For containers the same as Append.

name: Dedup
description: Keeps the existing resource. Saves a new resource with a different name, e.g. adding a timestamps at the end.

name: name
description: Resource name. Interpolated.

name: reconcileAction
description: Reconcile action - what to do if a resource with the same name already exists. Defalut is ``Overwrite``.

name: contents
description: Resource contents. File contents elements are adapted to ``SupplierFactory`` and produced ``InputStream``s are contcatenated. Container contents elements are adapted to ConsumerFactory and the container is passed to their ``execute`` method.

name: merger
description: Merger for ``Merge`` reconcile action. Adapted to ``org.nasdanika.common.resources.Merger`` to execute actual merge.
